1
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:08,500
Wait...

2
00:00:08,770 --> 00:00:09,970
Why am I even...

3
00:00:10,300 --> 00:00:11,720
following that guy?

4
00:00:14,570 --> 00:00:15,570
Actually,

5
00:00:15,950 --> 00:00:17,080
it's not that weird.

6
00:00:18,280 --> 00:00:19,280
I mean...

7
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:21,780
he was just coming out of a bridal shop.

8
00:00:24,060 --> 00:00:25,740
Maybe he's into women too.

9
00:00:25,820 --> 00:00:27,530
It's a possibility.

10
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:31,280
I just don't want any trouble.

11
00:00:32,340 --> 00:00:35,500
Since we've hooked up,
I should at least know if he's "safe."

12
00:00:36,100 --> 00:00:38,150
I have a right to know!

13
00:00:42,860 --> 00:00:43,960
You...

14
00:00:44,030 --> 00:00:45,030
What are you doing here?

15
00:00:46,430 --> 00:00:47,610
Me? Oh, I was just...

16
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:50,940
passing by on my way home from work.

17
00:00:52,840 --> 00:00:53,840
Just a coincidence...

18
00:00:54,680 --> 00:00:55,880
Do you two know each other?

19
00:00:56,630 --> 00:00:57,630
Oh.

20
00:00:58,470 --> 00:00:59,470
Well, uh...

21
00:01:01,320 --> 00:01:04,080
Just play it cool, you idiot.

22
00:01:04,920 --> 00:01:05,790
No way, are you serious?

23
00:01:05,791 --> 00:01:08,050
You should've told me
you were seeing someone.

24
00:01:10,500 --> 00:01:11,940
Oh, no, it's not like that.

25
00:01:12,690 --> 00:01:13,690
Sorry.

26
00:01:15,340 --> 00:01:16,340
It's fine.

27
00:01:16,620 --> 00:01:18,410
I know what you're trying to say.

28
00:01:21,550 --> 00:01:22,550
This person...

29
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:24,020
is just a friend.

30
00:01:24,070 --> 00:01:24,590
Huh?

31
00:01:24,591 --> 00:01:25,871
My brother actually has friends?

32
00:01:26,050 --> 00:01:27,050
Wait...

33
00:01:27,050 --> 00:01:28,050
Brother?

34
00:01:28,740 --> 00:01:29,740
So that means...

35
00:01:30,830 --> 00:01:31,830
this woman is his sister?

36
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:36,000
"Unexpectedly Naughty Fukami"

37
00:01:36,010 --> 00:01:38,170
So I ended up getting invited inside.

38
00:01:40,980 --> 00:01:41,980
How's my brother...

39
00:01:42,010 --> 00:01:43,360
(Episode 3)
doing at the office?

40
00:01:43,490 --> 00:01:45,830
He's actually really well-regarded
in the tech department.

41
00:01:45,980 --> 00:01:47,630
That's a relief.

42
00:01:47,820 --> 00:01:52,029
He's reliable at home, but
when it comes to his social skills...

43
00:01:52,030 --> 00:01:53,490
Hey, watch it.

44
00:01:53,950 --> 00:01:58,190
I'm just glad to hear
he has a friend like you.

45
00:02:00,060 --> 00:02:02,700
Our parents passed away a long time ago,

46
00:02:03,150 --> 00:02:04,440
and with my divorce,

47
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:07,220
I've been a real handful for him.

48
00:02:08,590 --> 00:02:10,110
But I'm getting remarried now,

49
00:02:11,710 --> 00:02:14,340
which is why you were at the bridal shop.

50
00:02:14,550 --> 00:02:15,990
Oh, did my brother tell you?

51
00:02:16,550 --> 00:02:17,989
I needed to pick up some wedding catalogs,

52
00:02:17,990 --> 00:02:19,980
so I asked him to come along.

53
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:22,166
It's a bit embarrassing
going to those places alone.

54
00:02:22,190 --> 00:02:25,240
Sana, don't you have
to pick up Haruto soon?

55
00:02:25,370 --> 00:02:26,370
Oh!

56
00:02:27,820 --> 00:02:31,150
Well, take good care of my brother! See ya!

57
00:02:37,780 --> 00:02:38,780
Sorry about her.

58
00:02:38,900 --> 00:02:40,580
Once she starts talking, she doesn't stop.

59
00:02:41,640 --> 00:02:43,850
Sounds like you've had a pretty rough life.

60
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:46,890
It's fine.

61
00:02:46,891 --> 00:02:49,360
I just did what I had to
do after our parents died.

62
00:02:50,260 --> 00:02:51,470
Besides, I have my sister,

63
00:02:52,090 --> 00:02:53,830
and my nephew is really cute.

64
00:02:54,270 --> 00:02:55,270
You have a nephew?

65
00:02:56,940 --> 00:02:58,340
He's spirited, and he's cute.

66
00:03:06,550 --> 00:03:07,550
What about you?

67
00:03:08,060 --> 00:03:09,060
What about your parents?

68
00:03:11,020 --> 00:03:12,020
My family?

69
00:03:13,310 --> 00:03:15,500
My dad's still around,

70
00:03:16,350 --> 00:03:18,310
but my mom walked
out on us a long time ago.

71
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:22,600
(To Aki-kun)

72
00:03:27,140 --> 00:03:29,120
I wonder how she's doing these days.

73
00:03:30,070 --> 00:03:31,070
Wait...

74
00:03:31,650 --> 00:03:32,940
Why am I even telling him

75
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:34,680
all this stuff?

76
00:03:36,490 --> 00:03:37,490
I see.

77
00:03:45,790 --> 00:03:47,520
So this computer is like your partner?

78
00:03:48,570 --> 00:03:49,650
I guess you could say that.

79
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:51,440
I use it to develop games and stuff.

80
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:53,380
Wait, you actually make games?

81
00:03:55,470 --> 00:03:57,210
You don't really care, do you?

82
00:03:58,750 --> 00:04:01,010
It's fine, you don't have
to force a conversation.

83
00:04:03,190 --> 00:04:04,480
Wait, right here?

84
00:04:09,480 --> 00:04:10,990
For a guy like him,

85
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:13,400
this place is full of
people he cares about...

86
00:04:16,150 --> 00:04:18,090
and people who care about him.

87
00:04:20,690 --> 00:04:21,890
It's nothing like my life.

88
00:04:23,350 --> 00:04:24,620
Put your legs up.

89
00:04:25,670 --> 00:04:26,670
Wait...

90
00:04:27,730 --> 00:04:28,730
Ah...

91
00:04:35,650 --> 00:04:36,650
I don't know why,

92
00:04:37,910 --> 00:04:39,020
but today he feels...

93
00:04:39,910 --> 00:04:41,840
more real.

94
00:04:49,420 --> 00:04:50,690
You're so sensitive...

95
00:04:51,140 --> 00:04:52,140
right here.

96
00:04:56,540 --> 00:04:57,540
Stop...

97
00:04:57,670 --> 00:04:58,670
Ah...

98
00:04:59,110 --> 00:05:00,110
I'm gonna come...

99
00:05:03,690 --> 00:05:04,890
Then just go ahead.

100
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:18,180
The bed's so small...

101
00:05:21,300 --> 00:05:22,400
Give me your hand.

102
00:05:24,750 --> 00:05:26,050
The walls are thin here.

103
00:05:28,770 --> 00:05:30,040
I can't hold it in anymore...

104
00:05:33,320 --> 00:05:35,360
If only you were like me.

105
00:05:37,030 --> 00:05:38,980
If you were as empty as I am,

106
00:05:39,860 --> 00:05:42,020
I could take you even more roughly.

107
00:06:00,750 --> 00:06:01,950
Whoa...

108
00:06:03,990 --> 00:06:05,530
Hey, don't blame me for that.

109
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:10,240
Hahaha...

110
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:13,040
That's the first time I've
ever done that at my place.

111
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:16,140
When I'm with you,

112
00:06:16,550 --> 00:06:18,330
I don't feel like myself.

113
00:06:20,930 --> 00:06:21,930
You're so cute.

114
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:26,840
No, no, no... what am I saying?

115
00:06:27,330 --> 00:06:28,330
Here.

116
00:06:28,500 --> 00:06:29,960
This is my contact info.

117
00:06:30,850 --> 00:06:32,760
Just message me directly.

118
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:35,699
If you keep staring at me at the office,

119
00:06:35,700 --> 00:06:36,860
people are going to find out.

120
00:06:39,350 --> 00:06:40,350
Oh.

121
00:06:42,020 --> 00:06:44,380
I'll go wash this.

122
00:06:55,410 --> 00:06:56,610
(Fukami Yuu)
His name...

123
00:06:57,020 --> 00:06:58,780
How should I input it?
[TN: He's unsure how to "read" the first name]

124
00:07:01,430 --> 00:07:03,820
Whatever. I'll just put him in my phone

125
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:06,330
as "Loser." [Zero Point Man]

126
00:07:14,120 --> 00:07:15,120
Calm down.

127
00:07:15,760 --> 00:07:17,610
This is just an experiment.

128
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:22,600
(Kaji: It's Kaji. Want to grab a drink?)
(Loser: Why?)

129
00:07:22,670 --> 00:07:25,150
(Kaji: No reason. Here's the address.)
What do you mean, "why"?

130
00:07:25,710 --> 00:07:28,290
It's not like I actually want
to drink with a guy like him.

131
00:07:30,970 --> 00:07:35,920
I just... started thinking
he was kind of cute, I guess.

132
00:07:39,060 --> 00:07:40,100
What happened before

133
00:07:40,450 --> 00:07:41,450
was just a fluke.

134
00:07:41,810 --> 00:07:42,810
An accident.

135
00:07:44,370 --> 00:07:48,100
I'm going to prove that we're completely
incompatible in every way except for sex.

136
00:07:49,220 --> 00:07:50,820
I just ordered some stuff, is that okay?

137
00:07:51,750 --> 00:07:52,750
Yeah.

138
00:08:01,110 --> 00:08:02,110
See?

139
00:08:02,430 --> 00:08:03,980
The vibe is totally dead.

140
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:11,510
I thought you'd take me somewhere fancy.

141
00:08:13,460 --> 00:08:14,560
You seem like the type

142
00:08:15,030 --> 00:08:17,000
who'd hang out at those stylish spots.

143
00:08:18,340 --> 00:08:19,340
I...

144
00:08:19,430 --> 00:08:21,490
don't really have any
nice clothes to wear out.

145
00:08:24,570 --> 00:08:25,710
That's a relief.

146
00:08:25,980 --> 00:08:27,240
This place is pretty low-key.

147
00:08:29,500 --> 00:08:30,500
Wait, you actually

148
00:08:30,860 --> 00:08:31,980
worry about stuff like that?

149
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:33,980
That's actually...

150
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:35,080
kind of cute.

151
00:08:35,950 --> 00:08:37,340
No.

152
00:08:37,980 --> 00:08:39,280
He is not cute.

153
00:08:40,050 --> 00:08:41,750
That was close.

154
00:08:42,310 --> 00:08:45,080
Crisis averted.

155
00:08:48,030 --> 00:08:50,330
I should... probably head out.

156
00:08:58,460 --> 00:08:59,560
Wait...

157
00:09:00,550 --> 00:09:01,550
What are we doing?

158
00:09:10,690 --> 00:09:11,690
Ah...

159
00:09:12,350 --> 00:09:13,350
I...

160
00:09:14,470 --> 00:09:16,510
want to see your apartment.

161
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:22,320
Ah...

162
00:09:22,440 --> 00:09:25,240
It's a mess. Give me a second.

163
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:33,750
Hold on a second.

164
00:09:38,503 --> 00:09:40,440
What's the rush, you drunk?

165
00:09:42,590 --> 00:09:44,470
I'm not drunk.

166
00:09:45,160 --> 00:09:50,250
Well, I'm not interested in sleeping
with someone who's wasted.

167
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:53,140
So we're not doing it?

168
00:09:54,310 --> 00:09:56,350
I'm already... kind of turned on.

169
00:09:59,080 --> 00:10:00,730
You...

170
00:10:03,180 --> 00:10:04,180
Ah.

171
00:10:06,920 --> 00:10:08,160
What am I going to do with you?

172
00:10:08,660 --> 00:10:11,020
You're so sensitive.

173
00:10:12,660 --> 00:10:13,860
Look at this...

174
00:10:18,500 --> 00:10:20,040
My finger goes right in.

175
00:10:24,700 --> 00:10:26,200
Arching your back like that...

176
00:10:26,980 --> 00:10:27,980
You're so naughty.

177
00:10:31,470 --> 00:10:32,470
No.

178
00:10:33,590 --> 00:10:35,500
I want to really do it with you.

179
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:41,440
Ah, ah...

180
00:10:46,180 --> 00:10:47,350
Hey, you...

181
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:50,960
Is there anything you
want me to do for you?

182
00:10:52,020 --> 00:10:53,020
Where's this coming from?

183
00:10:53,460 --> 00:10:54,460
Asking all of a sudden.

184
00:10:55,290 --> 00:10:58,540
I just feel like I'm the only
one having a good time.

185
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:02,010
If there's something you want, just say it.

186
00:11:06,090 --> 00:11:07,090
When you've...

187
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:08,700
been drinking...

188
00:11:08,890 --> 00:11:10,830
are you the type who'll black out?

189
00:11:14,590 --> 00:11:16,910
Yeah, it happens pretty often.

190
00:11:18,423 --> 00:11:19,430
In that case...

191
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:21,780
I want to hear...

192
00:11:22,100 --> 00:11:23,580
you say my name.

193
00:11:26,460 --> 00:11:28,850
That's your thing?

194
00:11:30,250 --> 00:11:31,680
Wow, that's actually pretty normal.

195
00:11:33,450 --> 00:11:34,770
- Actually, never mind.
- Akihiro.

196
00:11:37,560 --> 00:11:38,660
Wait, how?

197
00:11:38,820 --> 00:11:40,020
My name...

198
00:11:42,270 --> 00:11:43,530
You knew it?

199
00:11:44,170 --> 00:11:45,349
Of course I know the name

200
00:11:45,350 --> 00:11:46,630
of the person I'm sleeping with.

201
00:11:48,740 --> 00:11:49,740
And your...

202
00:11:50,190 --> 00:11:51,190
name?

203
00:11:52,350 --> 00:11:53,450
How do you pronounce it?

204
00:11:58,880 --> 00:11:59,880
Yuu...

205
00:12:02,860 --> 00:12:03,860
No.

206
00:12:04,670 --> 00:12:05,940
Once you give it a name,

207
00:12:06,980 --> 00:12:08,600
it starts to mean something.

208
00:12:09,360 --> 00:12:11,640
This... whatever this feeling is.

209
00:12:13,770 --> 00:12:14,770
Yuu.

210
00:12:17,850 --> 00:12:18,850
Fukami...

211
00:12:20,500 --> 00:12:21,500
Yuu.

212
00:12:23,560 --> 00:12:24,560
That's all.

213
00:12:25,310 --> 00:12:26,590
If only I could keep him

214
00:12:27,340 --> 00:12:30,170
trapped in this room forever.

215
00:12:32,630 --> 00:12:33,630
If only morning

216
00:12:34,330 --> 00:12:35,880
would never come.

217
00:13:02,890 --> 00:13:04,290
Wait... where am I?

218
00:13:39,230 --> 00:13:40,676
(Next Episode)
Thanks for everything on Friday.

219
00:13:40,700 --> 00:13:41,719
Fukami!

220
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:42,729
Is that him?

221
00:13:42,730 --> 00:13:45,240
That Fukami guy is actually kind of cute.

222
00:13:46,310 --> 00:13:47,509
Don't be ridiculous.

223
00:13:47,510 --> 00:13:49,233
I'm not interested in that.

224
00:13:49,378 --> 00:13:50,213
What's going on?

225
00:13:50,990 --> 00:13:52,710
I think we should take a break for a while.
